OL,3,CChanging fiscal rules could enable
OL,4,C#50bn of extra borrowing for investment
OL,6,FFor most of the last 50 years, both
OL,7,Fpublic investment (government spending
OL,8,Fon infrastructure like roads,
OL,9,Frailways, schools, and hospitals) and
OL,10,Fprivate investment (business spending
OL,11,Fto expand) have been very low in the
OL,12,FUK relative to other countries.
OL,14,FMany economists will tell you this
OL,15,Ftrend desperately needs to be reversed
OL,16,Fif we want to kickstart economic
OL,17,Fgrowth, if we want better living
OL,18,Fstandards and if we want to generate
OL,19,Fthe tax revenues necessary to improve
OL,20,Fpublic services.
